{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "email-api-service-collection-2026",
		"name": "Email API Service",
		"description": "Postman collection for Lambda Email API Service deployed on AWS API Gateway.\n\n**Base URL**: {{base_url}}\n**Production URL**: https://futbzxg5x8.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com\n**Local Development**: http://localhost:8080\n\n**Authentication**:\n- Health check endpoint: No authentication required\n- All other endpoints: X-API-Key header required\n- API Key: {{api_key}}\n\n## API Structure\n- **Health Check**: Service health endpoint (no auth)\n- **Email Finder**: 2 endpoints for finding emails by name and domain\n- **Email Verification**: 5 endpoints for email verification (single, bulk, pattern generation)\n\n## Features\n- Find emails by contact name and company domain using Connectra VQL\n- Generate email pattern combinations\n- Verify emails using multiple providers (Truelist, IcyPeas)\n- Bulk email verification (up to 10,000 emails)\n- Single email verification\n- Pattern-based email generation and verification\n\n## Usage\n1. Set environment variables: `base_url`, `api_key`\n2. Test health endpoint first (no auth required)\n3. Find emails using GET /email/finder/\n4. Verify single emails using POST /email/single/verifier/\n5. Verify multiple emails using POST /email/bulk/verifier/\n6. Generate and verify email patterns using POST /email/verifier/",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
		"_exporter_id": "20572666"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Health Check",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Health Check",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/health",
							"host": [
								"{{base_url}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"health"
							]
						},
						"description": "Check service health status. Returns service name, version, and configuration diagnostics. No authentication required."
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "Health check endpoint (no authentication required)"
		},
		{
			"name": "Email Finder",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Find Emails",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "X-API-Key",
								"value": "{{api_key}}",
								"description": "API key for authentication"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/email/finder/?first_name=John&last_name=Doe&domain=example.com",
							"host": [
								"{{base_url}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"email",
								"finder",
								""
							],
							"query": [
								{
									"key": "first_name",
									"value": "John",
									"description": "Contact first name",
									"disabled": false
								},
								{
									"key": "last_name",
									"value": "Doe",
									"description": "Contact last name",
									"disabled": false
								},
								{
									"key": "domain",
									"value": "example.com",
									"description": "Company domain or website URL",
									"disabled": false
								},
								{
									"key": "website",
									"value": "",
									"description": "Company website URL (alias for domain)",
									"disabled": true
								}
							]
						},
						"description": "Find emails by contact name and company domain. Searches for contacts matching the provided first name and last name whose company website domain matches the provided domain/website. Only returns contacts that have email addresses."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Get Single Email",
